DataElement.preferredDefinition: A non-proprietary, third generation modelling language. The Unified Modeling Language is an open method used to specify, visualise, construct and document the artifacts of an object-oriented software-intensive system under development. The UML represents a compilation of "best engineering practices" which have proven successful in modelling large, complex systems.:A state of connectedness between people, objects, or events; to be associated or connected with something.:A connection between nodes in a graph._The smallest possible quantity.:The number of elements in a set._Generic value domain for a primitive java dataype that is an Integer (32-bit two's complement).
